<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    <title> CheckPoint: Vertical Spring</title>
    
      <p>A light spring with a force constant k is suspended from the ceiling as shown. A block of mass m is attached to it. Initially, the block is held so that the spring is not stretched. The block is then released. The acceleration due to gravity is g. 

</p>
      <br/>
    
    <img src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK71.PNG" alt="BK71.PNG" encrypturl="no"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <br/>
    
      <p>
Part 1. 
What is the maximum elongation of the spring in the subsequent motion of the block?
</p>
    
    <part loncapaid="12">
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="no" loncapaid="13" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice name="foil1" correct="false">
                  \(\frac{k}{mg}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil2" correct="false">
                  \( \frac{2k}{mg}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( \frac{k}{2mg}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \(\frac{mg}{k}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil5" correct="true">
                  \(\frac{2mg}{k}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil6" correct="false">
                  \(\frac{mg}{2k}\)
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
    <part loncapaid="14">
      
        <p>
Part 2. 
Eventually, after multiple up-and-down cycles, the block comes to rest. How much heat is generated during the motion of the block?
</p>
      
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="no" loncapaid="15" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice name="foil1" correct="false">

                  Zero
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil2" correct="true">
                  \( \frac{(mg)^2}{2k}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil3" correct="false">
                  \( \frac{2(mg)^2}{k}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil4" correct="false">
                  \(\frac{(mg)^2}{4k}\)
          </choice>
          <choice name="foil5" correct="false">
                  \(\frac{3(mg)^2}{4k}\)
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
      </problem>
</html>
